%h1 Pre-Deposit Considerations

-if Databank::Application.file_mode == Databank::FileMode::READ_ONLY
  .alert.alert-alert
    =SystemMessage.read_only_message.raw

.panel-group(id="license" role="tablist" aria-multiselectable="true")
  .panel.panel-default
    .panel-heading(role="tab" id="licenseHeading")
      %h4(class="panel-title")
        %a( role="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#license" href="#licensePanel" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="licensePanel" class="accordion-toggle collapsed" )
          %span( class="metadata-label" ) You will need to select a license for your dataset. (click to expand)
    .panel-collapse.collapse(id="licensePanel" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="licenseHeading" )
      .panel-body
        %p
          Datasets are complex objects, and understanding how copyright law applies to datasets is similarly complex.
          %br
          For more background on Research Data Copyright and Licensing, review our help section on the topic:
          %a(href="#{IDB_CONFIG[:root_url_text]}/help#license")
            Research Data Copyright and Licensing
          %br
          Your dataset license options in Illinois Data Bank are:
        =render partial: 'datasets/help/license_infographic'
        %p
          %a(href="https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/" target="_blank" ) Find out more about CCO
          %br
          %a(href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/" target="_blank" ) Find out more about CC BY
          %br
          %span(class="strong") If you choose to use a license.txt file, upload it with your other dataset files.

= render partial: 'grouping_panel'
= render partial: 'zipping_panel'
.panel-group(id="contact" role="tablist" aria-multiselectable="true")
  .panel.panel-default
    .panel-heading(role="tab" id="contactHeading")
      %h4(class="panel-title")
        %a( role="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#contact" href="#contactPanel" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="contactPanel" class="accordion-toggle collapsed" )
          %span( class="metadata-label" ) You will need to select a long-term primary contact for your dataset. (click to expand)
    .panel-collapse.collapse(id="contactPanel" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="contactHeading" )
      .panel-body
        =render partial: "select_contact_info"

.panel-group(id="embargo" role="tablist" aria-multiselectable="true")
  .panel.panel-default
    .panel-heading(role="tab" id="embargoHeading")
      %h4(class="panel-title")
        %a( role="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#embargo" href="#embargoPanel" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="embargoPanel" class="accordion-toggle collapsed" )
          %span( class="metadata-label" ) You will be offered the option to delay publication of your dataset. (click to expand)
    .panel-collapse.collapse(id="embargoPanel" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="embargoHeading" )
      .panel-body
        %p
          Due to publisher or other requirements, researchers may need to deposit their dataset but make it temporarily unavailable for download.
          %br
          For more guidance, review our help section on the topic:
          %a(href="#{IDB_CONFIG[:root_url_text]}/help#embargo") Delaying Publication of/embargoing your dataset
        %p
          By default, there is no publication delay.  Your other options are:
          =render partial: 'help/embargo_infographic'
%br
.indent
  %span( class="metadata-label" ) The Research Data Service has data publishing experts and we're here to help!
  %br
  %br
  %p
    Guidance will continue to be available to you throughout this process.  To
    =succeed "," do
      %a(href="#{IDB_CONFIG[:root_url_text]}/contact") contact us
    or to review any of this information, open the
    %a(href="#{IDB_CONFIG[:root_url_text]}/help" )
      %span(class="glyphicon glyphicon-question-sign")
      Help
    menu at the top of each page.
  %p
    For context-specific help, look for
    %a(href="#" )
      %span(class="glyphicon glyphicon-question-sign" tabindex="-1" )
      what's this?
    links near form elements.

%hr

-if Databank::Application.file_mode != Databank::FileMode::READ_ONLY
  .row
    .col-md-3.col-md-offset-9
      %button(type="button" class="btn btn-primary btn-block" onclick='window.location = "/datasets/new"' )
        Continue
        %span(class="glyphicon glyphicon-triangle-right" )
      %button(type="button" class="btn btn-danger btn-block" name="cancel" onclick='window.location = "/"' )
        %span(class="glyphicon glyphicon-remove" )
        Cancel
      %br
